&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Sister/ Charge Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust is an Academic Health Science Centre (AHSC) and the largest trust in the country. Our mission is to provide world class healthcare for our patients, through excellence in research, education and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is dedicated to improving health outcomes by delivering the highest quality integrated healthcare and service provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking for enthusiastic and highly motivated individuals to join our busy Central Outpatient department and the multidisciplinary team, at Imperial College Health Care Trust based in St Mary’s Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will be proactive, patient orientated, with a passion to continuously improving patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working in diverse clinical specialties which include ENT, Dermatology, Cardiology, Vascular, General Medicine and General Surgical clinics, haematology, gastro, Rheumatology, Orthotics, Hepatology, etc . The role is aimed to ensure the provision of expert evidence based practice in order to achieve high service quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working, mentoring and supporting the junior staffs and students within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous knowledge and experience in the health prevention and health promotion activities is essential along with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Emeka on 02033122161 or at s.emeka@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
